# How to work with the router setup

## Route Definitions

Define routes in `@/modules/common/constants/routes.ts`:

```typescript
export enum Routes {
  Home = '/',
  Dashboard = '/dashboard',
  ProjectDetails = '/project/:id',
}
```

## Route Usage

```typescript
import { Routes } from '@/modules/common/constants';
import { Link, useNavigate } from 'react-router-dom';

// In components
<Link to={Routes.Dashboard}>Dashboard</Link>

// Programmatic navigation
const navigate = useNavigate();
navigate(Routes.Dashboard);
```

## Protected Routes

Use template components for route guards:

- `AuthGuardTemplate` - requires authentication
- `CanAccessTemplate` - role-based access control
